00:05:49.150 --> 00:05:50.280
[laughter]

00:05:50.280 --> 00:05:55.610
The Victorians loved puns. They loved puns.
It's ridiculous how much they loved puns.

00:05:55.610 --> 00:06:01.110
You see a lot more of this. The pun is the
highest form of Victorian humor. The other

00:06:01.110 --> 00:06:06.380
cool thing is finding not just strange windows
into things like the beard movement, which

00:06:06.380 --> 00:06:12.669
was from 1840 to 1900, but inventions that
seemed like great ideas but for some reason

00:06:12.669 --> 00:06:14.010
never quite caught on.

