00:57:23.240 --> 00:57:31.120
When I talk to people who are interested in
the Victorian era and the aesthetic of it,

00:57:31.120 --> 00:57:36.500
or their steam pumps or whatever it is, there's
a sense of like the good old days when things

00:57:36.500 --> 00:57:43.120
were awesome. And I think the much scarier
notion is the fact that we have not changed.

00:57:43.120 --> 00:57:47.050
And the reason that's scary is because it
implies that the things that we suffer from

00:57:47.050 --> 00:57:53.160
now are constant. They're part of human nature
and we'll always suffer from them. And it's

00:57:53.160 --> 00:57:57.560
very difficult to learn how to deal with that
because we think, "Oh, if only there's this

00:57:57.560 --> 00:58:01.500
